<subSubSection id="A8DC4DC537EA59C29DDF34958720A402" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="0719A3DDAECE542C5A7F15EAC40DCE2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="009A8DA93AE98144AB587D96EA5BF872" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A range-restricted Balkan endemic species that occurs only in SW Bulgaria and NE Greece. Normally a plant of high altitude (over 1500 m) and reported so far from four Greek mountains (Falakro, Pangeo, Orvilos, Menikio; 
<bibRefCitation id="B61DF6E040CB390C5EB2C20BF74FE448" author="Anagnostopoulos, A." journalOrPublisher="ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667693" refString="Anagnostopoulos, A., Strid, A., 2002. Flora Hellenica 2. ARG Gantner Verlag KG, Ruggell" title="Flora Hellenica 2" year="2002">Anagnostopoulos and Strid 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and three Bulgarian ones (Slavyanka, Pirin, Central Rodopi; 
<bibRefCitation id="5122D38EE2C1126C101795E70324087F" author="Petrova, A." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="293 - 311" refId="B7669158" refString="Petrova, A., Vladimirov, V., 2010. Balkan endemics in the Bulgarian flora. Phytologia Balcanica 16 (2): 293 - 311" title="Balkan endemics in the Bulgarian flora" volume="16" year="2010">Petrova and Vladimirov 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Our three new populations appear to be at the easternmost border of the 
<normalizedToken id="65412B8D84226E6A5B4208DCA6D619DC" originalValue="species’s">species's</normalizedToken>
distribution and grow at the unusually low altitude of 787-1341 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
